All 6 tests pass. Here's a summary of the fix:

**Bug:** Off-by-one error in `src/utils.ts`, line 7.

```typescript
// Before (buggy) — stops one element short:
for (let i = 0; i < items.length - 1; i++) {

// After (fixed) — iterates over all elements:
for (let i = 0; i < items.length; i++) {
```

The condition `i < items.length - 1` caused the loop to exit before reaching the last index. For example, on a 3-element array (indices 0, 1, 2), the loop only ran for `i = 0` and `i = 1`, skipping index 2. Removing the `- 1` makes it iterate through all elements correctly.

